This magnificent horse chestnut stands about 40 to 45 feet (12/14m) high and 30 feet (9m) wide on the northwest corner of Clapham Common Westside beside the A3.  The tree is in abundant flower (I would call them candles) already and there is still a week or so to go to the beginning of May; April (especially the first half) has been especially warm after a lot of rain in January and February and for the UK as a whole is lining up to maybe being the hottest on record.  Candles are up to 9 inches; leaves up to 12 inches.
